# Forecast4U — Builder.io AI Rules

This project uses IBM Carbon Design System (@carbon/react) and Builder.io for visual editing.

## Always do this for every code change
- Add or update unit tests. Never skip this, even for small changes.
- Use Carbon components from `@carbon/react` instead of plain HTML where a Carbon equivalent exists.
- Register any new React components in `src/components/builder-registry.js`.
- Use `var(--cds-*)` Carbon tokens for colors and spacing — never hardcode values.

## Never do this
- Never make real network requests in test files — always mock with `vi.fn()`.
- Never import CSS directly from `@carbon/react` individual files — the global `@use '@carbon/react'` in `app.scss` handles it.
- Never use class components.
